Graduate Research Project — Neural Collaborative Filtering (Keras/TensorFlow)
- Designed and trained a neural network with dual embedding layers (users + items)
  for collaborative filtering on MovieLens-scale dataset (6,200+ user-movie pairs)
- Implemented embedding-based architecture with dropout regularization (0.2),
  achieving MAE of 0.67 on held-out test set
- Built end-to-end pipeline: data preprocessing → model training → prediction evaluation
Tech: Python, Keras, NumPy, pandas
